The guards were accosted by three men while protecting municipal workers along Link road. CAPE TOWN - Three security guards have been shot and wounded in Browns Farm in Philippi. The guards were accosted by three men while protecting municipal workers along Link Road. The police's Frederick van Wyk said: All the firearms were taken by the suspects and the guards were rushed to a nearby hospital for medical treatment. Cases of attempted murder and armed robbery have been opened for investigation. 